materials.name: Gray Iron Class 20 As-Cast
materials.notes: Most common gray iron grade for general applications. Excellent machinability, damping, and castability.

materials.name: Gray Iron Class 25 As-Cast
materials.notes: Standard grade for automotive and general engineering. Good strength-to-cost ratio.

materials.name: Gray Iron Class 30 As-Cast
materials.notes: Higher strength grade for structural applications. Predominantly pearlitic matrix.

materials.name: Gray Iron Class 35 As-Cast
materials.notes: High strength gray iron for heavy-duty applications. Alloyed for strength.

materials.name: Gray Iron Class 40 As-Cast
materials.notes: High-strength alloyed gray iron for demanding applications.

materials.name: Gray Iron Class 45 As-Cast
materials.notes: Very high strength gray iron. Heavily alloyed for maximum strength.

materials.name: Gray Iron Class 50 As-Cast
materials.notes: Highest strength standard gray iron. Contains significant carbides.

materials.name: Gray Iron Class 60 As-Cast
materials.notes: Maximum strength gray iron. Significant carbide content affects machinability. Use rigid setup.

materials.name: High-Phosphorus Gray Iron As-Cast

damping_capacity.notes: EXCEPTIONAL damping - phosphorus creates steadite phase

materials.notes: Exceptional vibration damping due to phosphide eutectic (steadite). Best for machine tool bases.

materials.name: Gray Iron Class 30 Stress Relieved

heat_treatment.purpose: Eliminate casting stresses for dimensional stability

materials.notes: Stress relieved for dimensional stability. Essential for precision applications.

materials.name: Gray Iron Class 40 Flame Hardened

kienzle.note: Values for hardened surface - core is lower

materials.notes: Surface hardened for wear resistance. Machine before hardening when possible. Use CBN/ceramic for finished surfaces.

materials.name: Gray Iron Class 40 Induction Hardened

heat_treatment.purpose: Precise localized hardening with controlled depth

materials.notes: Induction hardening provides precise, controlled case depth. Superior to flame hardening for precision parts.

materials.name: Gray Iron High-Chrome Wear Resistant As-Cast

machinability.notes: EXTREMELY DIFFICULT. CBN/PCBN only. Grinding preferred.

materials.notes: High-chrome white iron for severe abrasion. 30-40% hard carbides. Extremely difficult to machine - use grinding.
